{ The move recommended by theory. } 8. exd5
{ After   8.e5  a6  9.Nc3  Bg4  followed by ...e7-e6, Black keeps the position closed and equalizes more easily. }
8... a6
{ Obviously, the immediate recapture 8... Qxd5 was not possible because of the fork on c7.  8... a6 is an important move to recover the d5-pawn, as   8...Nf6  allowed White to hang on to it with  9.c4 }
9. Nc3 Nf6
{ Theory asserts that Black regains the pawn and that he will be able to equalize easily here thanks, in particular, to the bishop pair. This is true for the recovery of the pawn, but for the rest it is not so simple. White can still cause him numerous problems. }
10. d4
