{ The most natural square for the queen, but two other retreats,  3... Qd8  and    3... Qd6  are also possible. The second alternative has recently gained some popularity. After    3... Qd6 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 a6  if not,   6.Nb5  can be unpleasant    , White can play  6. g3  to fianchetto his king's bishop. The bishop will be very good on the long diagonal, and after castling White could threaten Bf4, or even Ne5-c4, with a pleasant position. }
